{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018WtRq7zeWYM3FtLD39VQkt","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me compile my final report:\n\n## Summary: Cloche End-to-End Run Flow\n\nI've thoroughly explored the Cloche codebase and mapped how runs work end-to-end. Here's the complete picture:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Domain Types - `internal/domain/run.go`\n\n**Key Structure: `Run`**\n- **ID**: Unique identifier (generated via `domain.GenerateRunID()`)\n- **State**: `RunStatePending`, `RunStateRunning`, `RunStateSucceeded`, `RunStateFailed`, `RunStateCancelled`\n- **ActiveSteps**: Currently executing step names\n- **StepExecutions**: Array of `StepExecution` (name, result, timestamps, logs, git ref)\n- **Timestamps**: `StartedAt`, `CompletedAt`\n- **ContainerID**: Docker container running the workflow\n- **BaseSHA**: Git HEAD at run start (for result branch creation)\n- **ContainerKept**: Retention policy (failed runs or `--keep-container` flag)\n- **ErrorMessage**: Failure reason\n\n**Key Methods:**\n- `Start()` → transitions to `RunStateRunning`\n- `RecordStepStart(stepName)` → tracks step execution\n- `RecordStepComplete(stepName, result)` → marks step done\n- `Complete(state)` → finalizes run state\n- `Fail(msg)` → marks failed with error\n\n---\n\n## 2. Ports/Interfaces - `internal/ports/store.go`\n\n**RunStore Interface:**\n- `CreateRun(ctx, run)` → Creates new run in database\n- `GetRun(ctx, id)` → Retrieves run by ID\n- `UpdateRun(ctx, run)` → Persists run state changes\n- `DeleteRun(ctx, id)` → Removes run and step executions\n- `ListRuns(ctx, since)` → Lists all runs (optionally filtered by time)\n- `ListRunsByProject(ctx, projectDir, since)` → Lists project-specific runs\n- `ListProjects(ctx)` → Discovers all projects with runs\n\n**CaptureStore Interface:**\n- `SaveCapture(ctx, runID, exec)` → Records step execution details\n- `GetCaptures(ctx, runID)` → Retrieves all step executions for a run\n\n**LogStore & EvolutionStore:** Supporting stores for log files and code evolution tracking\n\n---\n\n## 3. SQLite Adapter - `internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go`\n\n**Implementation Details:**\n- **File Path**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go`\n- **Connection**: WAL mode, busy timeout 5s, single open connection for serialization\n- **Tables:**\n  - `runs`: (id, workflow_name, state, active_steps, started_at, completed_at, project_dir, error_message, container_id, base_sha, container_kept)\n  - `step_executions`: (run_id, step_name, result, started_at, completed_at, logs, git_ref, ...)\n  - `log_files`: (run_id, step_name, file_type, file_path, file_size, created_at)\n  - `evolution_log`: Evolution tracking\n  - `merge_queue`: Merge queue state\n\n**Key Methods:**\n- All RunStore methods map to SQL queries\n- `GetRun()` reconstructs full Run object from database\n- `UpdateRun()` uses `SetActiveStepsFromString()` for serialization\n- `FailStaleRuns()` marks orphaned runs as failed on daemon restart\n\n---\n\n## 4. CLI Commands - `cmd/cloche/`\n\n**Main Entrypoint: `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go`**\n\n**Commands:**\n| Command | Function | Flow |\n|---------|----------|------|\n| `run` | Launch workflow | gRPC `RunWorkflow()` → returns run ID |\n| `status` | Check run state | gRPC `GetStatus()` → displays state, active steps, errors |\n| `logs` | Stream logs | gRPC `StreamLogs()` or SSE `/api/runs/{id}/stream` |\n| `poll` | Wait for completion | Loops `GetStatus()`, detects terminal states |\n| `list` | Show recent runs | gRPC `ListRuns()` (default: last hour) |\n| `stop` | Cancel run | gRPC `StopRun()` |\n| `orchestrate` | Manual host workflow | gRPC `Orchestrate()` |\n\n**Run Command Flow:**\n1. Parse `--workflow`, `--prompt`, `--keep-container` flags\n2. Read workflow file to extract container image\n3. Call `client.RunWorkflow()` with `RunWorkflowRequest`\n4. Print returned `RunId`\n\n**Status Command Flow:**\n1. Call `client.GetStatus(runID)` \n2. Parse `GetStatusResponse` and display formatted output\n3. Shows: run ID, workflow name, state, container ID, active steps, error message\n\n---\n\n## 5. Daemon & gRPC Service - `cmd/cloched/main.go`, `internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`\n\n**Daemon Entry Point: `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go`**\n\n**Initialization:**\n1. Loads global config (`~/.config/cloche/config`)\n2. Opens SQLite database (default: `cloche.db`)\n3. Marks stale runs as failed on startup: `store.FailStaleRuns()`\n4. Initializes container runtime (Docker or Local)\n5. Creates gRPC server on Unix socket (`unix:///tmp/cloche.sock`) or TCP\n6. Optional: Starts HTTP web dashboard on configurable port\n7. Auto-executes host workflows for projects with `active = true`\n\n**Proto Definitions: `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`**\n\n| RPC | Request | Response | Purpose |\n|-----|---------|----------|---------|\n| `RunWorkflow` | workflow_name, project_dir, image, prompt, keep_container | run_id | Create and launch new run |\n| `GetStatus` | run_id | GetStatusResponse (state, active_step, step_executions, container status) | Poll run progress |\n| `StreamLogs` | run_id, step_name filter, log_type filter | stream of LogEntry | Stream logs (full, script, llm) |\n| `ListRuns` | all flag | RunSummary[] | List runs (all or last hour) |\n| `StopRun` | run_id | empty | Cancel running workflow |\n| `DeleteContainer` | container_id | empty | Remove retained container |\n| `Shutdown` | empty | empty | Graceful daemon shutdown |\n| `Orchestrate` | project_dir | dispatched count | Run host workflow orchestration |\n\n**Server Implementation: `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`**\n\n**RunWorkflow RPC Flow:**\n1. Generate unique run ID (retry on collision, reuse if >1 hour old)\n2. Write custom prompt to `.cloche/{run-id}/prompt.txt`\n3. Create Run in database with `RunStatePending`\n4. **Launch in background goroutine:**\n   - Auto-rebuild image if Dockerfile changed\n   - Call `container.Start()` with `ContainerConfig`\n   - Update run with `RunStateRunning` and container ID\n   - Call `trackRun()` to monitor\n\n**trackRun() Flow:**\n1. Attach to container stdout via `container.AttachOutput()`\n2. Parse JSON-line status messages from agent:\n   - `step_started` → `run.RecordStepStart()`\n   - `step_completed` → `run.RecordStepComplete()`\n   - `log` messages → broadcast to live subscribers\n3. Wait for container exit: `container.Wait()`\n4. **Extract outputs:**\n   - Copy step output files from container to `.cloche/{run-id}/output/`\n   - Capture full container logs to `container.log`\n   - Index log files in `log_files` table\n5. **Extract results to git branch:**\n   - Call `docker.ExtractResults()` to create `cloche/{run-id}` branch\n   - Uses `BaseSHA` for merge base\n6. **Finalize run state:**\n   - Parse reported result or exit code to determine success/failure\n   - Update run state in database\n7. **Container retention:**\n   - Failed runs: always keep\n   - `--keep-container`: keep\n   - Successful: remove\n8. Fire evolution trigger (if configured)\n\n**GetStatus RPC Flow:**\n1. Fetch run from database\n2. Check container liveness via `container.Inspect()`\n3. Load step executions from `captures` store (or run object)\n4. Return full status with timing and container state\n\n**ListRuns RPC Flow:**\n1. Query runs (all or since 1 hour ago)\n2. Convert to `RunSummary` protobuf messages\n3. Return sorted by start time (descending)\n\n---\n\n## 6. Agent Code - Container Workflow Execution\n\n**Agent Entry Point: `/workspace/cmd/cloche-agent/main.go`** (not fully shown, but referenced)\n\n**Agent Runner: `/workspace/internal/agent/runner.go`**\n\n**RunnerConfig:**\n```go\nWorkflowPath string        // path to .cloche/<workflow>.cloche\nWorkDir      string        // /workspace in container\nStatusOutput io.Writer     // write status messages to stdout\nRunID        string        // for logging\n```\n\n**Runner.Run() Flow:**\n1. Parse workflow DSL from `WorkflowPath`\n2. Create `StatusWriter` (JSON-line encoder to stdout)\n3. Initialize agent adapters (generic for scripts, prompt for Claude)\n4. Create unified log writer (`logstream.Writer`)\n5. Instantiate `stepExecutor` with adapters and log stream\n6. Create `engine.Engine` with executor\n7. **Engine.Run()**:\n   - Walks workflow step graph\n   - For each step: `executor.Execute(step)` → returns result name\n   - Fires status handlers on step start/complete\n   - Follows wiring to next steps based on results\n   - Collects terminal result (\"succeeded\", \"failed\", custom)\n8. Report final status: `statusWriter.RunCompleted(result)`\n9. Append history markers to `.cloche/history` file\n\n**Status Message Protocol: `/workspace/internal/protocol/status.go`**\n\nJSON-line format written to stdout:\n```json\n{\"type\":\"step_started\",\"step_name\":\"plan\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-10T...\"}\n{\"type\":\"step_completed\",\"step_name\":\"plan\",\"result\":\"success\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-10T...\"}\n{\"type\":\"run_completed\",\"result\":\"succeeded\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-10T...\"}\n```\n\n**Message Types:**\n- `step_started` → Agent about to execute step\n- `step_completed` → Step finished with result\n- `run_completed` → Workflow finished with final result\n- `log` → Arbitrary log message\n- `error` → Error message\n\n---\n\n## 7. Web Portal - `internal/adapters/web/`\n\n**Web Handler: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`**\n\n**Routes:**\n| Method | Path | Purpose |\n|--------|------|---------|\n| GET | `/` | Project overview (health, recent runs) |\n| GET | `/runs` | List all runs (filterable by project) |\n| GET | `/runs/{id}` | Run detail page (timeline, logs, container state) |\n| GET | `/projects/{name}` | Project detail (workflows, config, health) |\n| GET | `/api/projects` | JSON: All projects |\n| GET | `/api/runs` | JSON: Runs list |\n| GET | `/api/runs/{id}` | JSON: Full run details |\n| GET | `/api/runs/{id}/stream` | **SSE: Live log stream** |\n| DELETE | `/api/runs/{id}/container` | Delete retained container |\n| GET | `/api/projects/{name}/...` | Project info, workflows, step content |\n\n**Live Streaming (SSE): `handleAPIStream()`**\n\n**For Active Runs:**\n1. Subscribe to `logBroadcast` channel (published by daemon)\n2. Stream log lines as JSON SSE events: `data: {\"timestamp\":\"...\",\"type\":\"llm\",\"content\":\"...\"}\\n\\n`\n3. On context close or stream finish: send `event: done`\n\n**For Completed Runs:**\n1. Read archived `full.log` from `.cloche/{run-id}/output/full.log`\n2. Parse log lines via regex: `[timestamp] [type] content`\n3. Send each line as SSE event\n4. Send `event: done` with final run state\n\n**Log Types Parsed:**\n- `full_log`: Entire execution transcript\n- `llm`: Claude API streaming (parsed from raw JSON)\n- `script_log`: Shell command output\n- `status`: Workflow engine events\n\n---\n\n## 8. Host Executor - Orchestration\n\n**Host Runner: `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go`**\n\n**Purpose:** Execute `.cloche/host.cloche` (orchestration workflow) on the host machine\n\n**Runner.Run() Flow:**\n1. Parse `host.cloche` (must be workflow named \"main\")\n2. Generate unique run ID for host workflow\n3. Create output directory: `.cloche/{orchRunID}/output/`\n4. Instantiate `Executor` (implements `engine.StepExecutor`)\n5. Create engine and run workflow\n\n**Host Executor: `/workspace/internal/host/executor.go`**\n\n**Step Types Supported:**\n- **script**: Run shell command on host\n  - Environment: `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR`, `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT`, `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT`, mapped vars\n  - Extracts result marker: `CLOCHE_RESULT:<name>`\n  - Writes output to `.cloche/{orchRunID}/output/{step}.output`\n  \n- **workflow**: Dispatch container workflow run and wait for completion\n  - Calls `Dispatcher.RunWorkflow()` (gRPC to daemon)\n  - Polls `Store.GetRun()` until terminal state\n  - Maps run state (succeeded→success, failed→fail)\n  - Writes run ID to step output for downstream reference\n\n**Output Mapping (Wires):**\n- Reads previous step output\n- Evaluates JSON path expressions (via `OutputPath`)\n- Passes extracted values as environment variables to next step\n\n---\n\n## 9. Key Data Flow: Run Creation to Completion\n\n**1. User Initiates Run**\n```\nCLI: cloche run --workflow myworkflow\n  → gRPC: RunWorkflow(workflow_name, project_dir, image, prompt)\n  → Daemon: Create Run, launch container in background\n  → CLI: Print run ID, return\n```\n\n**2. Daemon Monitors Container**\n```\nDaemon (background):\n  → Start container with workflow mounted\n  → Attach to stdout\n  → Parse JSON-line status messages from agent\n  → Update Run.ActiveSteps, StepExecutions on each message\n  → Save captures to database\n  → Broadcast to live subscribers\n  → Wait for container exit\n```\n\n**3. Agent Executes Workflow**\n```\nAgent (in container):\n  → Parse .cloche/<workflow>.cloche\n  → Walk step graph\n  → For each step: Execute (script/agent/etc)\n  → Write status message: JSON-line to stdout\n  → Repeat until terminal step\n  → Write final status: run_completed\n```\n\n**4. User Monitors Progress**\n```\nOption A (CLI polling):\n  cloche status <run-id>\n    → gRPC: GetStatus(run_id)\n    → Daemon: Fetch from database, check container liveness\n    → Display state, active steps, completed steps with timing\n\nOption B (CLI streaming):\n  cloche logs <run-id> --follow\n    → HTTP SSE: GET /api/runs/{id}/stream\n    → Daemon: Stream from logBroadcaster or archived full.log\n    → Display formatted log lines\n\nOption C (Web portal):\n  http://localhost:8080/runs/{id}\n    → HTTP: Fetch run details, display timeline\n    → Optional SSE: Stream live updates\n```\n\n**5. Run Completes**\n```\nDaemon:\n  ✓ Agent reports final result (or container exit code)\n  ✓ Extract step outputs from container\n  ✓ Save container logs\n  ✓ Index log files in database\n  ✓ Extract results to git branch (cloche/{run-id})\n  ✓ Update Run.State to succeeded/failed\n  ✓ Apply container retention policy\n  ✓ Fire evolution trigger (if configured)\n  ✓ Close broadcast channel (signals web subscribers)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 10. File Organization Summary\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` | Run, RunState, StepExecution types |\n| `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go` | Step, Wire, OutputPath types |\n| `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` | RunStore, CaptureStore, LogStore interfaces |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` | SQLite implementation of all stores |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` | gRPC service implementation (RunWorkflow, GetStatus, etc) |\n| `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` | CLI client (run, status, logs, poll, list, stop) |\n| `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go` | Daemon startup and configuration |\n| `/workspace/cmd/cloche-agent/main.go` | Agent entrypoint (in-container) |\n| `/workspace/internal/agent/runner.go` | Agent workflow execution orchestration |\n| `/workspace/internal/protocol/status.go` | Status message protocol (JSON-line) |\n| `/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go` | Workflow step graph executor (both container and host) |\n| `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go` | Host workflow orchestration (host.cloche) |\n| `/workspace/internal/host/executor.go` | Host step executor (script, workflow dispatch) |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` | Web dashboard HTTP handlers and SSE streaming |\n| `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto` | gRPC service definitions |\n\nAll files are in READ-ONLY mode as requested. The exploration is complete and comprehensive."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a7a815c2a347b3d83 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 65647\ntool_uses: 31\nduration_ms: 73221</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4396f712-f062-4883-ba52-ad58e85081ed","uuid":"af336278-7760-4efd-be94-0061c2606117","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore this Go codebase thoroughly to understand how runs work end-to-end. I need to understand:\n\n1. The domain types for Run (internal/domain/)\n2. The ports/interfaces for RunStore\n3. The adapters for stores (sqlite)\n4. The CLI command for `run` and `status` (cmd/cloche/)\n5. The daemon/gRPC service definitions (proto files)\n6. The agent code that reports status back\n7. The web portal code that shows run details\n8. The host executor code\n\nFind all relevant files and report their paths and key structures. Focus on how a run is created, stored, and displayed.","agentId":"a7a815c2a347b3d83","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me compile my final report:\n\n## Summary: Cloche End-to-End Run Flow\n\nI've thoroughly explored the Cloche codebase and mapped how runs work end-to-end. Here's the complete picture:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Domain Types - `internal/domain/run.go`\n\n**Key Structure: `Run`**\n- **ID**: Unique identifier (generated via `domain.GenerateRunID()`)\n- **State**: `RunStatePending`, `RunStateRunning`, `RunStateSucceeded`, `RunStateFailed`, `RunStateCancelled`\n- **ActiveSteps**: Currently executing step names\n- **StepExecutions**: Array of `StepExecution` (name, result, timestamps, logs, git ref)\n- **Timestamps**: `StartedAt`, `CompletedAt`\n- **ContainerID**: Docker container running the workflow\n- **BaseSHA**: Git HEAD at run start (for result branch creation)\n- **ContainerKept**: Retention policy (failed runs or `--keep-container` flag)\n- **ErrorMessage**: Failure reason\n\n**Key Methods:**\n- `Start()` → transitions to `RunStateRunning`\n- `RecordStepStart(stepName)` → tracks step execution\n- `RecordStepComplete(stepName, result)` → marks step done\n- `Complete(state)` → finalizes run state\n- `Fail(msg)` → marks failed with error\n\n---\n\n## 2. Ports/Interfaces - `internal/ports/store.go`\n\n**RunStore Interface:**\n- `CreateRun(ctx, run)` → Creates new run in database\n- `GetRun(ctx, id)` → Retrieves run by ID\n- `UpdateRun(ctx, run)` → Persists run state changes\n- `DeleteRun(ctx, id)` → Removes run and step executions\n- `ListRuns(ctx, since)` → Lists all runs (optionally filtered by time)\n- `ListRunsByProject(ctx, projectDir, since)` → Lists project-specific runs\n- `ListProjects(ctx)` → Discovers all projects with runs\n\n**CaptureStore Interface:**\n- `SaveCapture(ctx, runID, exec)` → Records step execution details\n- `GetCaptures(ctx, runID)` → Retrieves all step executions for a run\n\n**LogStore & EvolutionStore:** Supporting stores for log files and code evolution tracking\n\n---\n\n## 3. SQLite Adapter - `internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go`\n\n**Implementation Details:**\n- **File Path**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go`\n- **Connection**: WAL mode, busy timeout 5s, single open connection for serialization\n- **Tables:**\n  - `runs`: (id, workflow_name, state, active_steps, started_at, completed_at, project_dir, error_message, container_id, base_sha, container_kept)\n  - `step_executions`: (run_id, step_name, result, started_at, completed_at, logs, git_ref, ...)\n  - `log_files`: (run_id, step_name, file_type, file_path, file_size, created_at)\n  - `evolution_log`: Evolution tracking\n  - `merge_queue`: Merge queue state\n\n**Key Methods:**\n- All RunStore methods map to SQL queries\n- `GetRun()` reconstructs full Run object from database\n- `UpdateRun()` uses `SetActiveStepsFromString()` for serialization\n- `FailStaleRuns()` marks orphaned runs as failed on daemon restart\n\n---\n\n## 4. CLI Commands - `cmd/cloche/`\n\n**Main Entrypoint: `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go`**\n\n**Commands:**\n| Command | Function | Flow |\n|---------|----------|------|\n| `run` | Launch workflow | gRPC `RunWorkflow()` → returns run ID |\n| `status` | Check run state | gRPC `GetStatus()` → displays state, active steps, errors |\n| `logs` | Stream logs | gRPC `StreamLogs()` or SSE `/api/runs/{id}/stream` |\n| `poll` | Wait for completion | Loops `GetStatus()`, detects terminal states |\n| `list` | Show recent runs | gRPC `ListRuns()` (default: last hour) |\n| `stop` | Cancel run | gRPC `StopRun()` |\n| `orchestrate` | Manual host workflow | gRPC `Orchestrate()` |\n\n**Run Command Flow:**\n1. Parse `--workflow`, `--prompt`, `--keep-container` flags\n2. Read workflow file to extract container image\n3. Call `client.RunWorkflow()` with `RunWorkflowRequest`\n4. Print returned `RunId`\n\n**Status Command Flow:**\n1. Call `client.GetStatus(runID)` \n2. Parse `GetStatusResponse` and display formatted output\n3. Shows: run ID, workflow name, state, container ID, active steps, error message\n\n---\n\n## 5. Daemon & gRPC Service - `cmd/cloched/main.go`, `internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`\n\n**Daemon Entry Point: `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go`**\n\n**Initialization:**\n1. Loads global config (`~/.config/cloche/config`)\n2. Opens SQLite database (default: `cloche.db`)\n3. Marks stale runs as failed on startup: `store.FailStaleRuns()`\n4. Initializes container runtime (Docker or Local)\n5. Creates gRPC server on Unix socket (`unix:///tmp/cloche.sock`) or TCP\n6. Optional: Starts HTTP web dashboard on configurable port\n7. Auto-executes host workflows for projects with `active = true`\n\n**Proto Definitions: `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`**\n\n| RPC | Request | Response | Purpose |\n|-----|---------|----------|---------|\n| `RunWorkflow` | workflow_name, project_dir, image, prompt, keep_container | run_id | Create and launch new run |\n| `GetStatus` | run_id | GetStatusResponse (state, active_step, step_executions, container status) | Poll run progress |\n| `StreamLogs` | run_id, step_name filter, log_type filter | stream of LogEntry | Stream logs (full, script, llm) |\n| `ListRuns` | all flag | RunSummary[] | List runs (all or last hour) |\n| `StopRun` | run_id | empty | Cancel running workflow |\n| `DeleteContainer` | container_id | empty | Remove retained container |\n| `Shutdown` | empty | empty | Graceful daemon shutdown |\n| `Orchestrate` | project_dir | dispatched count | Run host workflow orchestration |\n\n**Server Implementation: `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`**\n\n**RunWorkflow RPC Flow:**\n1. Generate unique run ID (retry on collision, reuse if >1 hour old)\n2. Write custom prompt to `.cloche/{run-id}/prompt.txt`\n3. Create Run in database with `RunStatePending`\n4. **Launch in background goroutine:**\n   - Auto-rebuild image if Dockerfile changed\n   - Call `container.Start()` with `ContainerConfig`\n   - Update run with `RunStateRunning` and container ID\n   - Call `trackRun()` to monitor\n\n**trackRun() Flow:**\n1. Attach to container stdout via `container.AttachOutput()`\n2. Parse JSON-line status messages from agent:\n   - `step_started` → `run.RecordStepStart()`\n   - `step_completed` → `run.RecordStepComplete()`\n   - `log` messages → broadcast to live subscribers\n3. Wait for container exit: `container.Wait()`\n4. **Extract outputs:**\n   - Copy step output files from container to `.cloche/{run-id}/output/`\n   - Capture full container logs to `container.log`\n   - Index log files in `log_files` table\n5. **Extract results to git branch:**\n   - Call `docker.ExtractResults()` to create `cloche/{run-id}` branch\n   - Uses `BaseSHA` for merge base\n6. **Finalize run state:**\n   - Parse reported result or exit code to determine success/failure\n   - Update run state in database\n7. **Container retention:**\n   - Failed runs: always keep\n   - `--keep-container`: keep\n   - Successful: remove\n8. Fire evolution trigger (if configured)\n\n**GetStatus RPC Flow:**\n1. Fetch run from database\n2. Check container liveness via `container.Inspect()`\n3. Load step executions from `captures` store (or run object)\n4. Return full status with timing and container state\n\n**ListRuns RPC Flow:**\n1. Query runs (all or since 1 hour ago)\n2. Convert to `RunSummary` protobuf messages\n3. Return sorted by start time (descending)\n\n---\n\n## 6. Agent Code - Container Workflow Execution\n\n**Agent Entry Point: `/workspace/cmd/cloche-agent/main.go`** (not fully shown, but referenced)\n\n**Agent Runner: `/workspace/internal/agent/runner.go`**\n\n**RunnerConfig:**\n```go\nWorkflowPath string        // path to .cloche/<workflow>.cloche\nWorkDir      string        // /workspace in container\nStatusOutput io.Writer     // write status messages to stdout\nRunID        string        // for logging\n```\n\n**Runner.Run() Flow:**\n1. Parse workflow DSL from `WorkflowPath`\n2. Create `StatusWriter` (JSON-line encoder to stdout)\n3. Initialize agent adapters (generic for scripts, prompt for Claude)\n4. Create unified log writer (`logstream.Writer`)\n5. Instantiate `stepExecutor` with adapters and log stream\n6. Create `engine.Engine` with executor\n7. **Engine.Run()**:\n   - Walks workflow step graph\n   - For each step: `executor.Execute(step)` → returns result name\n   - Fires status handlers on step start/complete\n   - Follows wiring to next steps based on results\n   - Collects terminal result (\"succeeded\", \"failed\", custom)\n8. Report final status: `statusWriter.RunCompleted(result)`\n9. Append history markers to `.cloche/history` file\n\n**Status Message Protocol: `/workspace/internal/protocol/status.go`**\n\nJSON-line format written to stdout:\n```json\n{\"type\":\"step_started\",\"step_name\":\"plan\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-10T...\"}\n{\"type\":\"step_completed\",\"step_name\":\"plan\",\"result\":\"success\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-10T...\"}\n{\"type\":\"run_completed\",\"result\":\"succeeded\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-10T...\"}\n```\n\n**Message Types:**\n- `step_started` → Agent about to execute step\n- `step_completed` → Step finished with result\n- `run_completed` → Workflow finished with final result\n- `log` → Arbitrary log message\n- `error` → Error message\n\n---\n\n## 7. Web Portal - `internal/adapters/web/`\n\n**Web Handler: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`**\n\n**Routes:**\n| Method | Path | Purpose |\n|--------|------|---------|\n| GET | `/` | Project overview (health, recent runs) |\n| GET | `/runs` | List all runs (filterable by project) |\n| GET | `/runs/{id}` | Run detail page (timeline, logs, container state) |\n| GET | `/projects/{name}` | Project detail (workflows, config, health) |\n| GET | `/api/projects` | JSON: All projects |\n| GET | `/api/runs` | JSON: Runs list |\n| GET | `/api/runs/{id}` | JSON: Full run details |\n| GET | `/api/runs/{id}/stream` | **SSE: Live log stream** |\n| DELETE | `/api/runs/{id}/container` | Delete retained container |\n| GET | `/api/projects/{name}/...` | Project info, workflows, step content |\n\n**Live Streaming (SSE): `handleAPIStream()`**\n\n**For Active Runs:**\n1. Subscribe to `logBroadcast` channel (published by daemon)\n2. Stream log lines as JSON SSE events: `data: {\"timestamp\":\"...\",\"type\":\"llm\",\"content\":\"...\"}\\n\\n`\n3. On context close or stream finish: send `event: done`\n\n**For Completed Runs:**\n1. Read archived `full.log` from `.cloche/{run-id}/output/full.log`\n2. Parse log lines via regex: `[timestamp] [type] content`\n3. Send each line as SSE event\n4. Send `event: done` with final run state\n\n**Log Types Parsed:**\n- `full_log`: Entire execution transcript\n- `llm`: Claude API streaming (parsed from raw JSON)\n- `script_log`: Shell command output\n- `status`: Workflow engine events\n\n---\n\n## 8. Host Executor - Orchestration\n\n**Host Runner: `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go`**\n\n**Purpose:** Execute `.cloche/host.cloche` (orchestration workflow) on the host machine\n\n**Runner.Run() Flow:**\n1. Parse `host.cloche` (must be workflow named \"main\")\n2. Generate unique run ID for host workflow\n3. Create output directory: `.cloche/{orchRunID}/output/`\n4. Instantiate `Executor` (implements `engine.StepExecutor`)\n5. Create engine and run workflow\n\n**Host Executor: `/workspace/internal/host/executor.go`**\n\n**Step Types Supported:**\n- **script**: Run shell command on host\n  - Environment: `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR`, `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT`, `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT`, mapped vars\n  - Extracts result marker: `CLOCHE_RESULT:<name>`\n  - Writes output to `.cloche/{orchRunID}/output/{step}.output`\n  \n- **workflow**: Dispatch container workflow run and wait for completion\n  - Calls `Dispatcher.RunWorkflow()` (gRPC to daemon)\n  - Polls `Store.GetRun()` until terminal state\n  - Maps run state (succeeded→success, failed→fail)\n  - Writes run ID to step output for downstream reference\n\n**Output Mapping (Wires):**\n- Reads previous step output\n- Evaluates JSON path expressions (via `OutputPath`)\n- Passes extracted values as environment variables to next step\n\n---\n\n## 9. Key Data Flow: Run Creation to Completion\n\n**1. User Initiates Run**\n```\nCLI: cloche run --workflow myworkflow\n  → gRPC: RunWorkflow(workflow_name, project_dir, image, prompt)\n  → Daemon: Create Run, launch container in background\n  → CLI: Print run ID, return\n```\n\n**2. Daemon Monitors Container**\n```\nDaemon (background):\n  → Start container with workflow mounted\n  → Attach to stdout\n  → Parse JSON-line status messages from agent\n  → Update Run.ActiveSteps, StepExecutions on each message\n  → Save captures to database\n  → Broadcast to live subscribers\n  → Wait for container exit\n```\n\n**3. Agent Executes Workflow**\n```\nAgent (in container):\n  → Parse .cloche/<workflow>.cloche\n  → Walk step graph\n  → For each step: Execute (script/agent/etc)\n  → Write status message: JSON-line to stdout\n  → Repeat until terminal step\n  → Write final status: run_completed\n```\n\n**4. User Monitors Progress**\n```\nOption A (CLI polling):\n  cloche status <run-id>\n    → gRPC: GetStatus(run_id)\n    → Daemon: Fetch from database, check container liveness\n    → Display state, active steps, completed steps with timing\n\nOption B (CLI streaming):\n  cloche logs <run-id> --follow\n    → HTTP SSE: GET /api/runs/{id}/stream\n    → Daemon: Stream from logBroadcaster or archived full.log\n    → Display formatted log lines\n\nOption C (Web portal):\n  http://localhost:8080/runs/{id}\n    → HTTP: Fetch run details, display timeline\n    → Optional SSE: Stream live updates\n```\n\n**5. Run Completes**\n```\nDaemon:\n  ✓ Agent reports final result (or container exit code)\n  ✓ Extract step outputs from container\n  ✓ Save container logs\n  ✓ Index log files in database\n  ✓ Extract results to git branch (cloche/{run-id})\n  ✓ Update Run.State to succeeded/failed\n  ✓ Apply container retention policy\n  ✓ Fire evolution trigger (if configured)\n  ✓ Close broadcast channel (signals web subscribers)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 10. File Organization Summary\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` | Run, RunState, StepExecution types |\n| `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go` | Step, Wire, OutputPath types |\n| `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` | RunStore, CaptureStore, LogStore interfaces |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` | SQLite implementation of all stores |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` | gRPC service implementation (RunWorkflow, GetStatus, etc) |\n| `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` | CLI client (run, status, logs, poll, list, stop) |\n| `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go` | Daemon startup and configuration |\n| `/workspace/cmd/cloche-agent/main.go` | Agent entrypoint (in-container) |\n| `/workspace/internal/agent/runner.go` | Agent workflow execution orchestration |\n| `/workspace/internal/protocol/status.go` | Status message protocol (JSON-line) |\n| `/workspace/internal/engine/engine.go` | Workflow step graph executor (both container and host) |\n| `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go` | Host workflow orchestration (host.cloche) |\n| `/workspace/internal/host/executor.go` | Host step executor (script, workflow dispatch) |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` | Web dashboard HTTP handlers and SSE streaming |\n| `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto` | gRPC service definitions |\n\nAll files are in READ-ONLY mode as requested. The exploration is complete and comprehensive."}],"totalDurationMs":73221,"totalTokens":65647,"totalToolUseCount":31,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":480,"cache_read_input_tokens":60646,"output_tokens":4521,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":480},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
