{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context. The summary below covers the earlier portion of the conversation.\n\nSummary:\n1. Primary Request and Intent:\n   The user requested implementing a feature to add run title/summary to the Cloche system. Specific requirements:\n   - Title passed explicitly via `cloche run --title \"title goes here\"` (e.g., from a ticket title)\n   - If not provided, cloche-agent generates a one-line summary from the prompt's request (via simple extraction)\n   - Title stored with the run in the daemon/store\n   - Displayed in `cloche status` CLI output\n   - Shown in the web portal's run-details header section\n   - Tests must be written and `go test ./...` must pass before reporting success\n   - Report CLOCHE_RESULT:success or CLOCHE_RESULT:fail when finished\n\n2. Key Technical Concepts:\n   - Hexagonal architecture (domain/ports/adapters)\n   - Go module with three binaries: cloche (CLI), cloched (daemon), cloche-agent (in-container)\n   - gRPC communication between CLI and daemon\n   - Protocol buffer definitions and generated Go code\n   - JSON-line status protocol between agent and daemon (via container stdout)\n   - SQLite storage with idempotent schema migrations (ALTER TABLE)\n   - SSE streaming for web portal live logs\n   - Workflow DSL for step-based execution\n\n3. Files and Code Sections:\n   - `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go`\n     - Core domain type for runs. Added `Title string` field to `Run` struct.\n     ```go\n     Title string // One-line summary of the work being done\n     ```\n\n   - `/workspace/internal/protocol/status.go`\n     - Status message protocol between agent and daemon. Added `MsgRunTitle` message type and `RunTitle()` method.\n     ```go\n     MsgRunTitle MessageType = \"run_title\"\n     \n     func (s *StatusWriter) RunTitle(title string) {\n         s.write(StatusMessage{Type: MsgRunTitle, Message: title})\n     }\n     ```\n\n   - `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`\n     - Proto definitions. Added `title` field to `RunWorkflowRequest` (field 6), `GetStatusResponse` (field 10), and `RunSummary` (field 7).\n\n   - `/workspace/api/clochepb/cloche.pb.go`\n     - Generated protobuf Go code. Manually added `Title` field with protobuf tags and `GetTitle()` getter methods to `RunWorkflowRequest`, `GetStatusResponse`, and `RunSummary` structs. Could not regenerate via protoc (not available in environment).\n     ```go\n     // In RunWorkflowRequest:\n     Title string `protobuf:\"bytes,6,opt,name=title,proto3\" json:\"title,omitempty\"`\n     // In GetStatusResponse:\n     Title string `protobuf:\"bytes,10,opt,name=title,proto3\" json:\"title,omitempty\"`\n     // In RunSummary:\n     Title string `protobuf:\"bytes,7,opt,name=title,proto3\" json:\"title,omitempty\"`\n     ```\n\n   - `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go`\n     - SQLite store implementation. Added `title` column migration, updated `CreateRun`, `GetRun`, `UpdateRun`, and all list query methods to include title. Used `replace_all` for most SELECT queries but had to manually fix `ListRunsSince` queries.\n     ```go\n     `ALTER TABLE runs ADD COLUMN title TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT ''`,\n     ```\n     All SELECT queries updated to include `COALESCE(title,'')` and all Scan calls updated to include `&run.Title`.\n\n   - `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`\n     - gRPC server. Updated `RunWorkflow` to set `run.Title = req.Title`, `trackRun` to handle `MsgRunTitle` (only sets title if empty, preserving explicit title), `GetStatus` to include title in response, `ListRuns` to include title in summaries.\n     ```go\n     case protocol.MsgRunTitle:\n         if run.Title == \"\" {\n             run.Title = msg.Message\n         }\n     ```\n\n   - `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go`\n     - CLI client. Added `--title` flag parsing in `cmdRun`, title display in `cmdStatus` (after Run ID), and title display in `cmdList` (truncated to 40 chars).\n     ```go\n     case \"--title\":\n         if i+1 < len(args) {\n             i++\n             title = args[i]\n         }\n     ```\n\n   - `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n     - Web dashboard handler. Added `Title` field to `apiRun` struct and `toAPIRun` function.\n\n   - `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html`\n     - Run detail template. Added title display in run metadata section.\n     ```html\n     {{if .Run.Title}}<dt>Title</dt><dd>{{.Run.Title}}</dd>{{end}}\n     ```\n\n   - `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html`\n     - Runs list template. Added Title column header, title cell in table rows, and title in JS polling. Updated colspan from 8 to 9.\n\n   - `/workspace/internal/agent/runner.go`\n     - Agent workflow runner. Added `extractTitle()` function that reads prompt.txt (from `.cloche/<runID>/prompt.txt` with fallback to `.cloche/prompt.txt`), extracts first non-empty line (stripping markdown headers), truncates to 100 chars. Calls `statusWriter.RunTitle(title)` before workflow execution.\n     ```go\n     func extractTitle(workDir string, runID string) string {\n         promptPath := filepath.Join(workDir, \".cloche\", runID, \"prompt.txt\")\n         if _, err := os.Stat(promptPath); err != nil {\n             promptPath = filepath.Join(workDir, \".cloche\", \"prompt.txt\")\n         }\n         // ... reads file, extracts first meaningful line, truncates to 100 chars\n     }\n     ```\n\n   - `/workspace/internal/domain/run_test.go` - Added `TestRunTitle` test\n   - `/workspace/internal/protocol/status_test.go` - Added `TestStatusWriter_RunTitle` test\n   - `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store_test.go` - Added `TestRunTitle` and `TestRunTitle_BackwardCompat` tests\n   - `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server_test.go` - Added 4 tests: `TestServer_RunWorkflow_WithTitle`, `TestServer_RunWorkflow_AgentGeneratesTitle`, `TestServer_RunWorkflow_ExplicitTitleNotOverriddenByAgent`, `TestServer_ListRuns_IncludesTitle`\n   - `/workspace/internal/agent/runner_test.go` - Added `TestRunner_ExtractsTitle` and `TestRunner_TitleTruncation` tests\n\n4. Errors and fixes:\n   - **SQLite `ListRunsSince` query mismatch**: After first test run, 2 tests failed (`TestListRunsSince` and `TestListRunsSinceEmpty`) with error `sql: expected 11 destination arguments in Scan, not 12`. The `replace_all` edit for SELECT queries only caught the single-line instances. The `ListRunsSince` function had its SELECT queries split across multiple lines with different formatting, so they weren't matched. The Scan calls WERE updated (they were single-line), causing 12 scan destinations but only 11 SELECT columns.\n     - Fix: Manually updated the two SELECT queries in `ListRunsSince` to add `COALESCE(title,'')`.\n   \n   - **protoc not available**: Could not regenerate protobuf Go code since protoc toolchain wasn't installed in the environment.\n     - Fix: Manually added `Title` fields with proper protobuf struct tags and `GetTitle()` getter methods to the generated Go structs. The raw binary descriptor was NOT updated, which means protobuf reflection won't know about the field, but direct struct access and the in-process test patterns used in this codebase work fine.\n\n5. Problem Solving:\n   - Successfully implemented the full title feature across all layers (domain, protocol, storage, gRPC, CLI, web, agent)\n   - Designed agent title extraction as simple first-line extraction from prompt.txt rather than LLM-based generation (keeping it simple)\n   - Ensured explicit `--title` takes priority over agent-generated title via `if run.Title == \"\"` guard in trackRun\n   - First test run showed 2 failures, which were fixed. Tests need to be re-run.\n\n6. All user messages:\n   - Initial request: \"Implement the following change in this project... Add run title/summary to CLI status and web portal\" with detailed requirements about `--title` flag, agent-generated fallback, storage, CLI display, and web portal display. Includes instruction to run `go test ./...` and report CLOCHE_RESULT:success or CLOCHE_RESULT:fail.\n\n7. Pending Tasks:\n   - Re-run `go test ./...` after fixing the `ListRunsSince` queries\n   - If tests pass, report CLOCHE_RESULT:success\n   - If tests fail, fix remaining issues and re-run\n\n8. Current Work:\n   I just fixed the `ListRunsSince` SELECT queries in `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` that were causing 2 test failures. The fix added `COALESCE(title,'')` to the two SELECT queries that were missed by the earlier `replace_all` edit. The first test run output was:\n   ```\n   --- FAIL: TestListRunsSince (0.00s)\n       store_test.go:168: sql: expected 11 destination arguments in Scan, not 12\n   --- FAIL: TestListRunsSinceEmpty (0.00s)\n       store_test.go:190: sql: expected 11 destination arguments in Scan, not 12\n   FAIL\tgithub.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/adapters/sqlite\t0.207s\n   ```\n   All other packages passed. The fix was applied and tests need to be re-run.\n\n9. Optional Next Step:\n   Re-run `go test ./... 2>&1` to verify the fix for `ListRunsSince` resolves the remaining test failures. If all tests pass, report CLOCHE_RESULT:success. The user's requirement states: \"You MUST run `go test ./... 2>&1` before reporting success. If any tests fail, fix the code until tests pass.\"\n\nIf you need specific details from before compaction (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /home/agent/.claude/projects/-workspace/4396f712-f062-4883-ba52-ad58e85081ed.jsonl\nContinue the conversation from where it left off without asking the user any further questions. Resume directly — do not acknowledge the summary, do not recap what was happening, do not preface with \"I'll continue\" or similar. Pick up the last task as if the break never happened."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_